# Migrating from `cnp-module-redis` to `terraform-module-azure-managed-redis`

Azure Managed Redis is a fully managed, enterprise-tier Redis service that replaces the
older Azure Cache for Redis (Standard/Premium) offering that `cnp-module-redis` provisions.
This guide explains the input/output differences and the steps needed to switch.

---
Example PR is provided to assist adoption of the new module. This should be used to get the new infrastructure up and running in alongside your current Redis in sandbox (side by side). Replacing your current resource block will _DELETE_ your current Redis instance.

Private endpoints are abstracted by the module as before.

Gotchas/troubleshooting at the bottom of this doc

Further information can be found by viewing this module's example folder, 'inputs-*.tf' files, the Azure documentation, terraform documentation or getting in touch with Platform Operations.

[Input files](https://github.com/hmcts/terraform-module-azure-managed-redis/blob/e018f031e653e66d226dbde406d7eb39c39e241e/inputs-optional.tf)

[Azure Managed Redis Docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/redis/)

[Terraform Managed Redis Docs](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/managed_redis)

## Feature parity
While MS is ending support for Az Cache for Redis, there is not complete feature parity between the offerings.

Please investigate + test these carefully as documentation from MS is hit or miss.

